menu "ESP LV Decoder"

config ESP_LV_DECODER_PJPG_HW_ALPHA_BLEND
    bool "PPA hardware alpha blending for transparent PJPG images (RGB888 displays)"
    default n
    help
        Offload alpha blending of transparent PJPG images to the PPA hardware on
        RGB888/XRGB8888 displays, instead of blending on the CPU. This frees the
        CPU during rendering of images with per-pixel transparency.

        It works by decoding such PJPG images to interleaved ARGB8888 (the format
        the PPA blend engine can composite in a single hardware op).

        When enabled (y):
        - Transparent PJPG images blend via PPA hardware (CPU offloaded).
        - Costs ~33% more image memory (4 B/px vs 3 B/px) and a one-time CPU
          interleave per decode, and increases PSRAM read bandwidth during blend.

        When disabled (n):
        - PJPG decodes to planar RGB565A8 (3 B/px); on RGB888 displays the blend
          is done on the CPU.

        RGB565 displays are unaffected (always RGB565A8). LVGL v9 only.

        Recommendation: keep enabled when the CPU is the bottleneck; disable on
        PSRAM-bandwidth-constrained panels where the extra read traffic hurts more
        than the freed CPU helps. Measure both.

endmenu
